    <p><img src="http://www.ostraining.com/images/drupal/Drupal-release-cycle.jpg" width="200" height="200" alt="Drupal release cycle" style="float: right;" />At the end of 2013, big changes were made to the Drupal release cycle.</p>

<p>You can read full details of the changes at <a href="https://drupal.org/node/2135189">https://drupal.org/node/2135189</a>.</p>
<p>The changes will start with Drupal 8, but are going to impact almost all current and future versions.</p>

<p>In this blog post, I'll give you a short, plain-English overview of the changes.<p> I'll show how the changes will impact users of Drupal 6, 7, 8 and 9.</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/ostrainingdrupal/~4/fYxliSR2_SQ" height="1" width="1"/>
